    "created_at": "2016-04-21T08:53:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-21T08:53:46Z",
    "body": "I hate to say this but I think we are encountering a bug of OS X here.\n\nUnder the hood Electron relies on `kevent` to get notified of the timer, in your perf-issue.js as example, we would call `kevent` with timeout of 10ms, so for every 10ms we would execute the timer. However when executing your code, it happens that sometimes `kevent` blocks for more than 10ms, even though we are passing 10ms as timeout, which results in large delay of the timer.\n\nI can't explain why it can happen.\n"
